[The possibility that Hurricane Katrina may exacerbate spread of ASR in the
southern states may be a factor in the coming weeks. Given that ASR is
widespread in those states and that kudzu is a perennial ASR host, the disease
could be a problem for soybean growers in the 2006 crop season.
